(secondQuint)Dermal Profile Analysis Using the NMR-MOUSE.

 Excretion of urine is impaired in terminal chronic kidney disease patients often requiring dialysis.

 Fluid management of dialysis patients is solely based on body weight differences before and after dialysis.

 Patients can suffer from either hypotension if too much fluid is eliminated by dialysis or from fluid-overload symptom (e.

g.

 shortness of breath, edema) if not enough fluid is eliminated.

 In this study a mobile non-invasive NMR-MOUSE setup (a nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy measurement) is used to measure the hydration status of the skin.

